=====
Introduction
=====

  The Clerics of Mitra maintain a position of prestige and
  power among the guilds of Darkwind. We are a benevolent
  guild focused around serving the ways of our goddess Mitra.
  For remaining obedient to her will, she grants our prayers
  when we call for her help by using our guild powers.

=====
Prospective Members
=====

 1. Race
 --------
  The follwing races may join our guild: dwarf, elf, faerie,
  gnome, halfling, or human. If you are not a member of
  one of these races you may change your race prior to joining
  by visiting the hall of races (refer to the newbie tome).

 2. Alignment
 ------------
  As a member of the guild, you will need to have your
  alignment at "good" or better in order for your spells to work.
  It is also important that your alignment be good or better
  when you initially try to join the guild.

 3. Weapon Specialization
 ------------------------
  Clerics can only wield blunt weapons without restricting
  their abilities.  It is recommended you train in at least
  "medium blunt." This is because one of our primary powers
  is to summon a hammer which is classified as a medium weapon.

 4. Armour Restrictions
 ----------------------
  At this point in time there are no armour restrictions
  for the Clerics of Mitra.

 5. Roleplay
 ------------
  The only forced roleplay within the guild is one's alignment.
  In order for spells to function the Cleric must be at least
  "good." In addition, the fellow Clerics have the ability to vote
  on a "ban" for certain people that defy the collective
  "guild interest." Once a ban is in place, Clerics are free to
  make their own decision, but are highly encouraged to follow
  the ban for the better good of the guild.

 6. Guild Powers
 ---------------
  Our powers are almost totally defensive. The heart of our skill
  lies in our ability to heal ourselves and others in varying
  fashions. In addition to being able to heal hit points, Clerics
  can also remove curses from weapons/armour and cure most forms
  of diseases known to Darkwind.  A premier power which a Cleric
  will possess from guild level 8 and above is the ability to
  summon a magical unique-class hammer. Although not everyone
  uses this as his/her primary weapon..it makes life after reboots
  a lot easier. For more specific info on our other spells, I would
  recommend checking <who> for Clerics and find out who the current
  GM is.  This would be a good place to start with questions,
  although any member really should be able to assist you.

=====
Conclusion
=====

  Hopefully now that you have read this, you have a general idea
  about how we function. We are a tight-knit group of friendly
  players that enjoy extremely functional guild powers. (We hardly
  ever are in a bind we cannot save ourselves from). If you think
  we sound like something you would enjoy, please join. If you
  are still undecided feel free to take your time and ask us
  plenty of questions.
